        "headline": "Special Weather Statement issued April 8 at 8:51PM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "description": "A front will bring snow to Point Hope Thursday afternoon through\nFriday morning. Southerly winds will gust upwards of 45 to 50 mph\nduring this time as well. There is a chance for some blowing snow\nat the onset but with temperatures rising near and above freezing\nThursday night, any blowing snow would be short lived. Snow\ntotals will be around 1 inch.",
