        "headline": "Special Weather Statement issued April 8 at 8:46PM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "description": "A front will bring a line of snow and rain Thursday afternoon\ninto Friday morning. The snow will be wet in nature as\ntemperatures rise up to 30F to 35F north/west of the Koyukuk River\nand up to 40F south of the Koyukuk River. Many locations,\nespecially away from the coast may mix with rain Thursday night.\nTotal snow accumulations will generally be around 1 to 3 inches.\n\nSoutherly winds along the coast will peak around 25 to 35 mph\nsouth of the Seward Peninsula, and 35 to 45 mph north of the\nSewa",
        "severity": "Moderate",
        "certainty": "Observed",
        "urgency": "Expected",
        "sender": "NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "effective": "2026-04-08T20:46:00-08:00",
        "expires": "2026-04-09T16:00:00-08:00",
        "areas": "South Slopes of the Western Brooks Range; Noatak Valley; Kivalina and Red Dog Dock; Lower Kobuk Valley; Baldwin Peninsula; Upper Kobuk Valleys; Southern Seward Peninsula Coast; Interior Seward Peninsula; Eastern Norton Sound and Nulato Hills; Yukon Delta Coast; Lower Yukon River; Lower Koyukuk Valley; Middle Yukon Valley; Lower Yukon and Innoko Valleys",
