      {
        "id": "urn:oid:2.49.0.1.840.0.59e6f04aa15551a8368e0d8ae72766b8226ad43f.001.1",
        "event": "Special Weather Statement",
        "headline": "Special Weather Statement issued April 8 at 8:44PM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "description": "Gusts through the Bering Strait Coast are expected to reach up to\n45 mph Thursday morning, with the highest gusts expected for St.\nLawrence Island, Wales, and Brevig Mission. Between 1-2 inches of\nsnow is expected for the area through Thursday.\n\nAnother round of precipitation is expected to begin Friday\nmorning, bringing another inch or so of snow. Mixed precipitation\nis possible with this second round, such as rain and freezing\nrain, as temperatures will be above freezing.",
        "severity": "Moderate",
        "certainty": "Observed",
